UPSTREAM SOURCE LICENSES

The benchmark records and reference corpus are derived from the following
sources. Each derivative record retains a `label_source` / source tag for
attribution.

* EBTI rulings (EU Binding Tariff Information) -- republished under the EU Open
  Data license. Derivative records retain `source = "EBTI"`. The CC BY-SA 4.0
  share-alike clause is inherited from EBTI.
* CROSS rulings (US CBP) -- US Customs and Border Protection rulings are in the
  public domain. Derivative records retain `source = "CROSS"`.
* Japan Customs advance rulings -- public advance rulings, retained with the
  `JP_CUSTOMS` source tag.
* Bill-of-lading (BOL) excerpts -- used for research with attribution; appear
  only in the product-description inputs (Tier 1 / Tier 2), never as raw
  shipment records.
* Catalog component data -- used for academic benchmarking; appears in the
  Tier 1 / Tier 2 inputs, classified after expert review. Brand/manufacturer
  names are confined to the structured `manufacturer` field and do not appear in
  model-facing description text.
